  "strategy_type_title_avg": "Average Cost Bots",
  "strategy_type_title": "Bot Type",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page1_title": "What is a spot grid bot",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page1_subtitle": "Newbie Friendly / Buy Low, Sell High / Volatile Market",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page1_desc": "Spot grid bots are automated trading bots that are designed to sell high and buy low in swinging markets. A bot will start to work for you once you have completed parameters setup. Once started, the bot will divide your investment into several parts, buying in stages when the prices are declining and selling in stages when prices are rising, continuously taking advantage of market fluctuations to achieve gains through buying low and selling high.",
  "strategy_guide_complete_tutorial": "View Full Tutorial",
  "strategy_guide_next": "Next",
  "strategy_guide_previous": "Previous",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page2_title": "Advantages of spot grid bots",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page2_desc": "The newbie-friendly spot grid bots don't have human emotions like fear or greed, avoiding panic selling that emotional decision-making causes in volatile markets. The bot operates round the clock. This makes sure no trading opportunity is missed out.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page2_desc1": "In volatile and rising market: users can achieve double profits from rising coin prices and volatility arbitrage.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page2_desc2": "In volatile and falling market: users can reduce losses through volatility arbitrage.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page3_title": "How to create a spot grid bot",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page3_desc": "There are three methods",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page3_desc1": "Copy a backtesting bot: A newbie can choose a 7-day/30-day/180-day backtesting bot in Recommended section. A backtesting bot has parameters setup based on historical market conditions and intelligent algorithms; ",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page3_desc2": "Follow a bot provider: If a backtesting bot does not meet your needs, you can filter out top performers in the Recommended section and follow a provider to trade;",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page3_desc3": "Customize your own bot: You can set parameters according to your judgment of market movement, and invest funds to start your own grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page4_title": "About the termination of spot grid bots",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page4_desc": "You can stop the spot grid bot at any time. Please note: ",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page4_desc1": " The crypto market is highly volatile and bots might not always adapt quickly to sudden market changes. If a spot grid bot does not match the current market conditions, it should be terminated timely to mitigate potential loss.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page4_desc2": " A spot grid bot is not deemed to work as a day trading bot. Instead, it requires a relatively long period of time to achieve its goal.",
  "strategy_guide_spotgrid_page4_desc3": " As a spot grid bot is typically buying low and selling high, its profit curve will show a tendency of declining first and rising later. Loss at the beginning is therefore theoretically considered normal.",
  "strategy_guide_start": "Start trading",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_label": "Volatile Market/Leverage Effect/Advanced",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page1_title": "What is Futures Grid?",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page1_paragraph1": "Futures Grid is a trading bot that trades in Perpetual Futures markets. The bot helps users to profit from both trends and fluctuations, suitable for short, medium and long-term investment in volatile markets.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page1_paragraph2": "Compared with spot grid that is typically of low capital utilization rate, low returns, and only allowing for trading with what is held, futures grid empowers users to trade on margin, thus increasing capital efficiency and potential profits. You can let the futures grid bot work for you by setting parameters such as side, leverage, price range and numbers of grids.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_title": "Advantages of Futures Grid",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_paragraph1": "In volatile markets, you can prioritize the futures grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_paragraph2": "1. Greater Capital Efficiency: The bot amplifies trading equity through leverage, thus increasing users' capital utilization.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_paragraph3": "2. Suitable for Multiple Market Conditions: Long grid bot is suitable for volatile and rising markets; short grid bot is suitable for volatile and falling markets; Neutral grid bot is suitable for users who are not sure about the direction of price movements in volatile markets.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_paragraph4": "3. Lower Fees: Futures grid enjoys lower trading fees. Compared with spot grid, futures grid has higher ROI per grid.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page2_paragraph5": "Tips: In markets with good liquidity, you can choose to trade with a futures grid bot instead of a spot grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_title": "How to trade with Futures Grid",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_paragraph1": "There are three methods:",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_paragraph2": "1. Copy a backtesting bot: A newbie can choose a 7-day/30-day/180-day backtesting bot in Recommended section. A backtesting bot has parameters setup based on historical market conditions and intelligent algorithms;",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_paragraph3": "2. Follow a bot provider: If a backtesting bot does not meet your needs, you can filter out top performers in the Recommended section and follow a provider to trade;",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_paragraph4": "3. Customize your own bot: You can set parameters according to your judgment of market movement, and invest funds to start your own grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page3_paragraph5": "Tips: As the coin price fluctuates, the higher the leverage, the higher the risk of liquidation.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page4_title": "How to terminate Futures Grid",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page4_paragraph1": "You can stop the futures grid bot at any time. Please note:",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page4_paragraph2": "1. The crypto market is highly volatile and bots might not always adapt quickly to sudden market changes. If a futures grid bot does not match the current market conditions, it should be terminated timely to mitigate potential loss.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page4_paragraph3": "2. A futures grid bot is not deemed to work as a day trading bot. Instead, it requires a relatively long period of time to achieve its goal.",
  "strategy_guide_futuregrid_page4_paragraph4": "3. Similar to the spot grid, a long/short futures grid bot is typically buying low and selling high, thus its profit curve will show a tendency of declining first and rising later. Loss at the beginning is therefore theoretically considered normal.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_label": "Rising in Volatility/Never Miss Chances/Newbie",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page1_title": "What is Infinite Grid?",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page1_paragraph1": "Infinite Grid is an advanced version of the Spot Grid. Compared with spot grid, infinite grid does not require users to set a highest price, allowing the user to hold their coins in volatile and rising markets and ensuring that traders never miss chances.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page1_paragraph2": "The grid places orders by equal price ratio. The logic is to sell more digital assets than the initial value each time when the price of the digital asset rises, and to buy the corresponding amount of the digital asset when the price falls, so that digital assets always maintain their initial value.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page2_title": "Advantages of Infinite Grid",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page2_paragraph1": "Infinite Grid is an ideal tool for traders who want to capitalize on market volatility and maximize their profits, ensuring that traders never miss chances.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page2_paragraph2": "1. Never Miss Chances: The bot can automatically buy low and sell high without the highest price, thus users can keep holding their coins while keeping selling additional assets, capitalizing on long-term market trends.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page2_paragraph3": "2. Swing Arbitrage: Compared with Hodlers, traders who trade with the infinite grid can arbitrage from the swing market through buying low and selling high.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_title": "How to trade with Infinite Grid",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_paragraph1": "There are three methods:",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_paragraph2": "1. Copy a backtesting bot: A newbie can choose a 7-day/30-day/180-day backtesting bot in Recommended section. A backtesting bot has parameters setup based on historical market conditions and intelligent algorithms;",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_paragraph3": "2. Follow a bot provider: If a backtesting bot does not meet your needs, you can filter out top performers in the Recommended section and follow a provider to trade;",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_paragraph4": "3. Customize your own bot: You can set parameters such as ROI per grid and amount/coin according to your judgment of market movement, and invest funds to start your own grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page3_paragraph5": "Tips: When the coin price falls below the lowest price, the bot will stop placing orders.",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page4_title": "How to terminate Infinite Grid",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page4_paragraph1": "You can terminate the infinite grid bot at any time, please note:",
  "strategy_guide_infinitegrid_page4_paragraph2": "The bot should be terminated timely when the coin you invested is consistently declining as the bot is more suitable for slow bullish markets.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_label": "Volatile Market / Short or Long / Advanced",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page1_title": "What is Margin Grid?",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page1_paragraph1": "Margin grid is an upgraded version of the spot grid. It combines the spot grid and margin trading. By margin borrowing, the trading power of invested principal will be amplified and thus lead to potential higher returns. With Margin Grid, users can go long or short to obtain profits in medium to long-term volatile markets.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page1_paragraph2": "A bot will start to work for you after you set parameters such as price range and numbers of grids. Once started, the bot will divide your investment into several parts, buying in stages when the prices are declining and selling in stages when prices are rising, continuously taking advantage of market fluctuations to achieve gains through buying low and selling high.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page2_title": "Advantages of Margin Grid",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page2_paragraph1": "In volatile markets, you can prioritize the margin grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page2_paragraph2": "1. Greater Capital Efficiency: The bot amplifies trading equity through leverage, thus increasing users' capital utilization.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page2_paragraph3": "2. Suitable for Multiple Market Conditions: Long grid bot is suitable for volatile and rising markets; short grid bot is suitable for volatile and falling markets.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page2_paragraph4": "3. Trade in Spot Market: Compared with perpetual futures markets, spot markets have better liquidity, thus the bot's PnL is less affected by the slippage.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page3_title": "How to trade with Margin Grid",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page3_paragraph1": "There are three methods:",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page3_paragraph2": "1. Copy a backtesting bot: A newbie can choose a 7-day/30-day/180-day backtesting bot in Recommended section. A backtesting bot has parameters setup based on historical market conditions and intelligent algorithms;",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page3_paragraph3": "2. Follow a bot provider: If a backtesting bot does not meet your needs, you can filter out top performers in the Recommended section and follow a provider to trade;",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page3_paragraph4": "3. Customize your own bot: You can set parameters according to your judgment of market movement, and invest funds to start your own grid bot.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page4_title": "How to terminate Margin Grid",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page4_paragraph1": "You can stop the margin grid bot at any time. Please note:",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page4_paragraph2": "1. The crypto market is highly volatile and bots might not always adapt quickly to sudden market changes. If a margin grid bot does not match the current market conditions, it should be terminated timely to mitigate potential loss.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page4_paragraph3": "2. A margin grid bot is not deemed to work as a day trading bot. Instead, it requires a relatively long period of time to achieve its goal.",
  "strategy_guide_margingrid_page4_paragraph4": "3. Similar to the spot grid, a long/short margin grid bot is typically buying low and selling high, thus its profit curve will show a tendency of declining first and rising later. Loss at the beginning is therefore theoretically considered normal.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_label": "Sector Rotation/Bottom Fishing/Advanced",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page1_title": "What is Smart Rebalance?",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page1_paragraph1": "Smart Rebalance is a medium and long term automatic trading bot that dynamically adjusts the asset allocation in your portfolio.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page1_paragraph2": "In volatile markets, your bot can maintain the preset asset allocation through rebalancing at preset portfolio proportion, intervals and thresholds.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page2_title": "Advantages of Smart Rebalance",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page2_paragraph1": "When you are bullish on the long-term development of multiple coins, Smart Rebalance is a good option.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page2_paragraph2": "1. Risk Diversification: The bot helps to manage risk by ensuring that the portfolio is diversified, effectively reducing the risk of drawdown due to putting all eggs in one basket.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page2_paragraph3": "2. Buy low, sell high: It's common to see sectors or different cryptocurrencies rotates to rise or fall in the crypto industry. In Smart Rebalance, when assets' prices go up or down, their shares of value in the portfolio change accordingly. Under such circumstance, the bot will automatically sell some of the asset with rising share of value at a high price and buy some of the other assets with falling share of value to bring the asset distribution in the portfolio to the initial setting and sell them when their prices take turn to rise. Through constant rebalancing, you can obtain long-term returns in rotations.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page3_title": "How to trade with Smart Rebalance",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page3_paragraph1": "There are two methods:",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page3_paragraph2": "1. Follow a bot provider/Copy a backtesting bot: You can filter out top performers or backtesting bots in the Recommended section and follow a provider or copy a bot to trade.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page3_paragraph3": "2. Customize your own bot: You can choose coins according to your judgment of market movement, and start your own bot by setting the bot's auto-rebalancing parameters.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page3_paragraph4": "Tips: Smart Rebalance can also be used in ETF",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page4_title": "How to terminate Smart Rebalance",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page4_paragraph1": "You can terminate Smart Rebalance at any time.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page4_paragraph2": "1. Smart Rebalance should be terminated timely when one or more coins are consistently declining.",
  "strategy_guide_smartrebalance_page4_paragraph3": "2. When the bot ends, the remaining coins will be transferred to your Spot Account. You can then decide whether to sell coins in the spot market or not.",
